        <Element Type="Comment" Id="07AB41CD">
            <Comment>
                GameHeart Initialization establishes the ObserverID (the player ID that observers will be using) and forces players to treat that ID as much like
                a normal observer as possible.  The observer ID is set in the &quot;Game UI Data&quot; data module and is set to 14 in GameHeart by default but
                can be overidden using another module if necessary and GameHeart should dynamically retrieve the correct ID.
                The Observer integer variable is the assigned Observer ID in data.  And the ObserverGroup variable is a player group containing only
                the observers.
                Because the observer ID system does not work identically to a normal observer, there are some overrides here to try to make it as
                similar as possible.  Locking the ally color setting to normal colors prevents observers from running into a problem where all players
                in the game appear as yellow.  This is caused by having the allied color setting on while using an observer ID.  We are just disabling
                it as an option.
                Some alliance settings may seem strange to include here, such as Shared Defeat and Shared Control, but it seems that some standard
                observer features are linked to these alliance settings somehow and they are required to create a normal observer experience.
                There are still some things that do not work when using an observer ID that work fine for normal observers, such as showing control
                groups and the number of harvesters currently mining a resource (in the unit info panel when selecting the resource itself, not on the bars 
                appearing above geysers or base buildings).  You can still see these things while using an Observer ID by switching specifically to that
                player&apos;s perspective, but you cannot see them in &apos;everyone view&apos;.
            </Comment>
        </Element>
