            <Comment>
                Sets Score values for the players to assist Observer UIs:
                - PlayerId - PlayerId of the player. There is no perfect way to get the PlayerId of a player in an Observer Interface. This allows using a PlayerId in e.g. 1vs1 where you usually only have Left/Right instead of the ID. Some frames require a PlayerId like the DataRefFrame and do not support the left/right side
                - PlayerStatus - Status of the player. E.g. players that left the game cannot be identified in Observer Interfaces. This is allows flagging of defeated players in team games
                - VersusModePlayerSide - L/R of the player based on spawn positions in 1vs1. Else when there are two teams, then team 1 is left and team 2 is right
