                - Broodlord Broodling timed life: unit Broodling, player 1, killer 1, deathType timeout, effect TimedLifeFate, damagePos 35.1646,38.8049
                - Hallucination timed life: unit Probe, player 1, killer 1, deathType normal, effect KillHallucination, damagePos 38.8967,39.9495
                - Auto Turret costs 100 resources for repairs, needs to be ignored in resources destroyed HANDLED
                - MULE costs 50 minerals =&gt; killing one should not raise that HANDLED
                - drone morphing structure cancelled: unit: Hatchery, player 1, killer 16, deathType cancel, effect , damagePos 0,0 &gt;&gt; structures&apos; refund cost needs to subtract the drone&apos;s costs as it survives and costs in unit data include it &lt;&lt;&lt; HANDLED
                - Zerg structures have their costs too high for refund calculation (drone survives =&gt; subtract drone resource costs) HANDLED
                - killing Overlord Transport does not add correct scores, only 100 minerals (TODO kill score and resources lost are likely to be wrong as well)
                Kill baneling cocoon =&gt; count not tracked, real costs of morph are refunded like cancelling it manually, but that was not detected atm (was counted like cocoon being killed)
                Overlord Cocoon resource costs are just wrong with 150 100
                Lurker Egg has no resource costs =&gt; should provide some
                =&gt; res destroyed for cocoons and evolution eggs are not using base unit&apos;s costs + refund damage TODO refund damage
                neural parasited units that die have the wrong owner (owner of unit wrong? TODO check if triggering player is better)
                abduct&apos;s placehoder is detected as unit death: unit Thor, player 1, killer 1, deathType remove, effect KillRemove, damagePos 21.9214,34.186
                - Larva finish morph: unit: Larva, player 1, killer 16, deathType , effect , damagePos 0,0
                - Larva cancels morph: unit: Larva, player 1, killer 16, deathType , effect , damagePos 0,0 &lt;&lt;&lt; well, sh*t :D TODO maybe detectable by morphing being cancelled? other morphs similar?
                - CC morph correctly refunds, even if killed
                - Hive/Lair/Spire morphing correctly refunds, even if killed
                - Zerg unit morphs refund correctly, even if killed
                - Protoss warp in units correctly refunds if power field is lost (does not refund if unit is killed with damage)
                TODO
                - Carrier with interceptors dies =&gt; resource cost of the carrier should be lower as there are 4 interceptors already included for free
            </Comment>
